 :language lawyer: /n./ A person, usually an experienced or senior software
engineer, who is intimately familiar with many or most of the numerous
restrictions and features (both useful and esoteric) applicable to one or
more computer programming languages. A language lawyer is distinguished by
the ability to show you the five sentences scattered through a 200-plus-page
manual that together imply the answer to your question "if only you had
thought to look there". Compare {wizard}, {legal}, {legalese}.